data.text:
Taylor Hale is the winner of Big Brother 24 (US)

Taylor entered the Big Brother house as one of the biggest underdogs of all time. With the entire house out to get her, she managed to escape the first eviction due to one of the fellow contestants walked from the house, cancelling the eviction. However, she still was the main target.

Weeks later, Taylor, alongside the Leftovers alliance, took over the game blindsiding Ameerah Jones & Nicole Layog solidifying herself as a power player in the game. As a result, she began a friendship with fellow Leftover Joseph Abdin and his shock eviction in the Split House Double Eviction led to her path to the end.

On Finale Night, Taylor's emotional speeches led her to victory over Monte Taylor by a 8-1 becoming the First Black Woman to win the Big Brother Crown, and became the first female civilian to win the show since Kaycee Clark's win in season 20. But only just a few minutes later, Taylor would also be the first contestant in American Big Brother history to win both the game and America's Favorite Houseguest bringing her season's winnings to over $800,000 in cash and prizes.
